Sun May 27 12:14:01 CEST 2007 <jurgenv@cwi.nl>
 * test/tables/Sdf2.tbl: regenerated this regression table. The bugfix in
   goto.c filters more reductions in Sdf2.tbl. The regression parse forest
   does not change with this different table. The speed of the parser does
   improve slightly. My analysis is that the follow restrictions on LAYOUT?
   in Sdf2.sdf are meant for speed; they filter conflicts and not actual
   ambiguity.

Sat May 26 10:05:26 CEST 2007 <jurgenv@cwi.nl>
 * src/goto.c: fixed bug #752. The filterReductions function applies follow
   restrictions by removing and splitting reductions on certain lookaheads.
   It was rewritten from a recursive function to an iterative loop earlier.
   The error occurred in situations where there were more multiple character
   lookahead restrictions for the same symbol, and also reductions possible 
   for a different symbol with the same lookahead (i.e. a reduce/reduce 
   conflict). In the old recursive code each restriction would limit the
   possible reductions for certain lookaheads more, while in the new code
   each restriction was applied to the original set of lookahead characters.
   Note: I'm having trouble producing a small regression test for this
   bug.

